Referral Business: The following business should be referred to echelon:

-	Policy periods in excess of 12 months (plus odd time)
-	Risks located outside of Quebec or Ontario
-	Flood/SBU coverage in High-Exposure Flood Zones
-	Any risk with commercial occupancies that have deep-fat frying without regularly serviced automatic fire suppression systems
-	Risks with roofs older than 25 years
-	Risks where electrical/plumbing/heating hasn’t been updated in the last 40 years, subject confirmation of:
o	No Poly B plumbing
o	No aluminium wiring, unless pigtailed.
-	Backdated coverage (no-loss letter required)
-	Subsidence and underpinned properties
-	Properties undergoing refurbishment where works over CAD 100,000 – see ‘Structural Alterations and Renovations’
-	Unprotected business 
-	Any insured with more than two claims in the past five years
-	Any insured with a fire claim in the past three years
-	Any insured with any claim over CAD 250,000 in the last three years


Please send all referrals to where should we send referrals? 



RISK LIMITS

CAD 3,000,000 any one risk (ceded to facility) including buildings, contents and loss of rents for Frame/Brick Veneer buildings.

CAD 5,000,000 any one risk (ceded to facility) including buildings, contents and loss of rents for Joisted Masonry/Better Construction buildings.


‘Any one risk’ deemed to be all exposures within the following minimum building separation (new business only):

Frame/Brick Veneer			75 feet
Joisted Masonry/Better Construction	50 feet


Maximum Participation

The maximum Echelon will participate on any one policy is 50% 

Minimum Sums Insured 

Buildings	CAD 250,000
Contents	CAD 10,000


RATING GUIDE

Minimum gross fire rate (excluding Earthquake) of 0.28% to be applied, except:
-	0.22% for Masonry Non-Combustible risks
-	0.15% for Fire-Resistive risks

Minimum gross fire rates for vacant business (excluding Earthquake) 

(Named Perils coverage only), 6 months term:

-	0.09% (Monthly) for Frame/Brick risks
-	0.08% (Monthly) for Masonry Non-Combustible risks
-	0.08% (Monthly) for Fire-Resistive risks


Earthquake Rating

-	0.02% for Frame/Brick risks
-	0.03% for Masonry Non-Combustible risks
-	0.03% for Fire-Resistive risks

Sewer Back-Up Rating

-	0.15% limits $100k, $150k or $250k
-	Capped at CAD 500 

Renewal Rating

Average portfolio rate increase of 5% to be achieved by end of contract term.

5% minimum inflationary asset increase to be applied (in absence of third-party valuation in last 12 months).


MINIMUM DEDUCTIBES

Any one event				CAD 5,000 
Water Damage				CAD 7,500
SBU					CAD 7,500 except CAD 25,000 when full policy limit
Flood 					CAD 25,000
Earthquake				10% (of TIV) or CAD 100,000 minimum


Credits for increased deductibles
-	10% credit (on fire rate) for CAD 10,000 deductible
-	15% credit (on fire rate) for CAD 25,000 deductible 
-	20% credit (on fire rate) for CAD 50,000 deductible
-	25% credit (on fire rate) for CAD 100,000 deductible


Credits for increased EQ deductibles

-	15% credit (on EQ rate) for 15% deductible
-	25% credit (on EQ rate) for 20% deductible
-	30% credit (on EQ rate) for 25% deductible

 
Extension of Property Coverages 

 

 
UNDERWRITING CONSIDERATIONS

Inspections

Here are the circumstances under which building inspections should be request:
-	Every building with a TIV > CAD 2m
-	If the building age is over 60 years old. 
-	If the plumbing and electrical are over 25 years old.
-	If the building has one or more insurance claims within the past 5 years.
-	If the building houses tenants that fall into categories from the following:
	Restaurants.
	Grocery/convenience stores 
	Any other building where inspections are requested by Echelon.

Locality

Particular attention to be paid to the aspects of buildings / type of use, etc. for risks located on St-Hubert Street in Montreal, "Plaza St-Hubert" located between Villeray Street and Rosemont Boulevard. If in doubt refer to Echelon. 

Particular attention to be paid to all risks located on Ste-Catherine East, Street (Montreal), between Jacques-Cartier Bridge and Vimont Street. Sector with poverty and social difficulties, building not well maintained, etc. Verify the quality of the risk and the owners / renters. In case of doubt, refer to Echelon. 


Structural Alterations and Renovations

Any property undergoing alterations or renovations must be notified prior to works commencing. 

Details required:
-	Estimated cost
-	Length of time the works will take
-	Whether planning permission required/obtained
-	Whether any changes to use of property
-	Whether value of property will increase
-	Confirmation contractor has liability insurance up to the full value of the property

Loading of 0.075%/month to be applied.





